review_text: A very demanding, well-equipped gym. It was a little crowded in the afternoons on weekdays.

review_text: Ive been coming here for a long time, but now that my pass has expired, Ill never do it again!! Practically, a complete school holds the physical education class, or I dont know what they are doing during school time, there is always a class of children who sweat all over, never use a towel, leave the weights where they just went and sit down in front of a machine where they talk on the phone for half an hour!!  The place became unpleasant!!  There are always more trainers downstairs, why dont they hire them??  It works like this in every normal place!!  Apart from me, I know 4 other people who go to another room for this reason....

Elvezhetetlen lett a hely!!  Lent van allandoan tobb edz  is azok miert nem szolnak rajuk??  Minden normalis helyen igy m kodik!!  Rajtam kivul meg 4 olyan embert tudok akik ezert mennek el masik terembe....

We booked the squash for two hours we AYCM  pass when we came she asked us to pay for the extra hour we told her that we usually book it for two hours with no problem she said she will ask (end of discussion). Went up to the court no lights were on had to go down 3 times to ask her to turn the lights on. First of all veeery rude receptionist and huge difference between when she talks with us (foreigners) with poker grumpy face and with hungarians and its not because of the language she speaks english well. We started at 13h30 she turned of the light at 15:00 and asked us for 4k we were late yes but there was 0 communication about the fee and being late. She didnt do her job and she kept arguing and blaming us. We play squash all over the city and usually receptionnists they communicate everything the rules but she didnt. Unfortunately its a good gym but I wont ever come back to this gym and I dont recommend it to foreigners. Whats a receptionist gets paid for if not for greeting EVEYONE EQUALLY and COMMUNICATING.

review_text: I have been coming to the hall for more than 6 years and so far I have been satisfied with everything except the reception... until TODAY. During individual training, my partners TRX rope broke and he fell to the ground on his back. Not a single coach went to him after seeing the incident!! When he took the rope over to the rec to show it, all he got was a roll of the eyes, Excuse me, are you okay? instead of It is understandable that everyone uses the equipment at their own risk, but if the hall leaves worn-out old equipment outside, there is a DANGER OF ACCIDENTS! You cant do anything, the serious and bleeding elbow injury obviously doesnt matter :( they cant take a report and they didnt find the complaint book - interesting way... The attitude of the reception girls was beyond quality, this should have been handled much more professionally! If you want to train SAFELY in a properly equipped gym in good condition, DO NOT CHOOSE THIS PLACE! We wont take any more, thank you.
